                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/10470: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Canton</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jenkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-06-03T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >June 3, 1929—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 3—10:48 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Cantonese naval forces occupied Wuchow last night without opposition. River will
                    be reopened to navigation immediately.</p>
                <p>Legation has been informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jenkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
